.TH "bee-install" "1" "2012-05-18" "bee @BEE_VERSION@" "bee - bau et einfach"

.SH "NAME"
bee\-install \- Install a bee package

.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.SY "bee install"
.OP options
.I <bee-package>
.YS

.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.P
.B bee-install
is used to install a bee package.
.P
Normally
.B bee-install
searches
.B BEE_PKGDIR
for
.I <bee-package>
but you can use
.BI /path/to/ <bee-package> .bee.tar.bz2
too.

.SH "OPTIONS"
.TP
.B \-\-verbose
.TQ
.B \-v
Run
.B bee-install
in verbose mode.
.TP
.B \-\-force
.TQ
.B \-f
Use
.B \-\-force
to prevent
.B bee-install
from checking whether
.I <bee-package>
is already installed.
.TP
.B \-\-help
.TQ
.B \-h
Print a little help screen.
.TP
.B \-\-update
.TQ
.B \-u
Update an install
.IR <bee-package> .
.TP
.B \-\-noop
Run
.B bee-install
in noop mode.

.SH "ENVIRONMENT"
.TP
.B BEE_PKGDIR
.RS
Directory searched for available bee packages

